resources.performance_tooltip1_1: Performance levels are expressed in terms of Database Transaction Units (DTUs) for single databases and elastic Database Transaction Units (eDTUs) for elastic pools. Learn more
resources.performance_tooltip3_1: Elastic Database Transaction Units or eDTUs represent the shared resources in an elastic pool and are a blended measure of CPU, memory, I/O (data and transaction log I/O). Learn more

resources.performance_tooltip2: Database Transaction Units or DTUs, are a blended measure of CPU, memory, I/O (data and transaction log I/O). The ratio amongst these resources was originally determined by an OLTP benchmark workload designed to be typical of real-world OLTP workloads.
